## Evidence Log

### Week 1–3 (May 2026) — Initial IC analysis

| Feature | IC (7d) | p-value | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| skill_ai_ml_velocity | -0.37 | 0.073 | ✓ Passes filter |
| trends_zscore | +0.25 | 0.547 | Promising — low N |
| skill_digital_share | +0.17 | 0.277 | Watch |
| skill_cloud_velocity | +0.08 | 0.695 | Needs more data |
| volume_zscore | +0.08 | 0.725 | Needs more data |

**Backtest (1 test week):**
- Accuracy: 60% vs 44% baseline
- Hit rate: 100% vs 63.6% null mean
- Top decile return: 3.20% vs 2.67% null
- p-value: 0.636 — not yet significant (expected)

**Revised understanding:**
The job posting volume signal (original hypothesis) is directionally correct 
but needs 15+ more weeks to confirm statistically. The skill velocity signals 
are more immediately informative than raw volume. The AI/ML velocity finding 
was a surprise and warrants deeper investigation.

---

## What Would Falsify This Hypothesis

1. After 20+ weeks, mean IC on volume_zscore remains below 0.02
2. Permutation test p-value stays above 0.20 with 10+ test weeks
3. High-confidence model picks consistently underperform low-confidence picks
4. The same signals applied to a different sector produce similar IC 
   (would suggest the signal is spurious, not IT-specific)

